{
  "texts": [
    "By amalgamating initial features with structural information, they stand as a potent option to attain commendable performance.",
    "The effectiveness of GNNs is contingent on the manner in which graphs are constructed from the available data.",
    "Existing models employ diverse approaches to generate graphs.",
    "For instance, the propagation graph is created based on the propagation of information, with the model having minimal direct involvement in graph generation.",
    "Conversely, the similarity graph encompasses various approaches, including criteria related to the similarity between information content or the features of users' profiles."
  ]
}